r cotton, malting barley, spring and winter wheat and potatoes\nwhich outweighed the price increases in apples, oranges and eggs.\nThe economic price measure showed a decline of 3.0 per cent\nlast week, resulting from expected cutbacks in industrial production\nand increasing stocks.\nWEEKLY STATISTICAL REPORT\nWks, end.\n1929-19.35 19.36-1945 Aug. Aug.\nHigh Low High Low 1926 equals 100 24 17 Chg.\nDomestic Purchasing Power\n181.? 100.9 128.5 86.24 Dollar in (w\u2019les\u2019e m\u2019rk\u2019ts).. 86.57 86.57 0.0\nDomestic Commodity Prices\n99.1 55.0 115.96 77.8 All comm'd\u2019t\u2019s (131 items).. 115.51 115.51 0.0\n99.8 47.7,121.6 68.5 Raw materials (35) 119.9 120.0 \u2014O.l\n101.1 54.0 106.8 76.4 Semim\u2019nuf\u2019ct'd goods (.30)..106.8 106.7 +O.l\n100.5 60.2 113.9 82.9 Finished goods (66) 113.7 113.7 0.0\n110.3 4.3.5 128.8 56.6 Farm products (20) 125.3 125.4 \u2014O.l\n104.8 54.8 125.3 72.3 Foodstuffs (25) 123.1 123.1 0.0\n1.35.3 55.1 158.8 94.3 Hides and leather (7) 152.0 152.0 0.0\n87.1 50.3 92.5 68.1 Fuel and lighting (8) 90.9 90.9 0.0\n99.0 45.0 113.3 60.2 Textiles (13) 113.2 113.2 0.0\n112.0 78.3 121.1 96.5 Metal products (16) 117.5 117.5 0.0\n98.3 86.0 119. R 79.1 Building m'terials (23) 120.0 119.6 0.3\n95.8 71.8 106.3 79.3 Chemicals (16) 103.6 10.3.6 0.0\n93.1 49.5 86.3 54.8 Miscellaneous (10) 86.3 86.3 0.0\nNew Indexes\n98.5 52.7 120.8 74.3 Ind't\u2019al raw mafri\u2019la (35).. 102.8 102.7 +O.l\n111.0 72.5 102.9 74.9 Foreign exchange rates 78.9 78.9 0.0\n88.2 42.3 102 J 62.2 Economic price measure.... 88.0 90.7 \u20143.0.\nNet l\nSale* in 100 High Ix>w Close Chg. j\n1 Howe Sound 58% 38% 38%+\n3 Hudson A Man 5% 5%\u2014\n2 Do pf 17 17 17\nHudson B MAS 28 27% 28\n88 Hudson Motor 31% 30% 30% 1%\n28 Hupp Motor 6% 6% 6%\n\n2 Idaho Power :.H 36 36\n16 Illinois Central 32% 32 32\nI 1 Do pf 60% W% 60%\ni 16 (ndpis PwALt 26% 26 26%\n5 Induat Rayon 56% 56 56 1\n1 Inger-Rand 118% 118% HB%\u2014\n4 Inland Steel 93% 93 93%\n\u25a0II Inspirit Con Cop 12% 12% 